The '''Ashy-crowned Sparrow-lark''' ('''''Eremopterix griseus''''') is a species of [[lark]] in the [[Alaudidae]] family.
It is found in [[Bangladesh]], [[India]], [[Nepal]], [[Pakistan]], and [[Sri Lanka]].
